{
  "title": "Jar-Fist",
  "pages": [
    {
      "lines": [
        "Jar-Fist",
        "",
        "In the northwestern reaches",
        "of the continent,",
        "deep within the mountains",
        "and dense forests—",
        "",
        "there was a renowned fighter.",
        "",
        "Sad-Fist.",
        "A human bandit,",
        "a madman of bare fists."
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        "His name came from",
        "the emotion left behind",
        "in those who gazed upon his fists.",
        "",
        "Sadness.",
        "",
        "He carried no weapons.",
        "With nothing but his hands,",
        "he crushed all things,",
        "and that was his creed."
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        "“I can do anything.",
        "I can break anything.”",
        "",
        "So he believed.",
        "",
        "One day,",
        "while wandering in search",
        "of the strong,",
        "he was drawn to a workshop",
        "filled with thick smoke."
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        "Clay and fire,",
        "and something",
        "he could not explain.",
        "",
        "There sat an old potter,",
        "feeding the kiln in silence.",
        "",
        "Then, he spoke.",
        "",
        "“What is it you seek,",
        "wanderer?”"
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        "Sad-Fist laughed.",
        "",
        "“I seek nothing.",
        "I already hold everything—",
        "within these fists.”",
        "",
        "The potter did not answer.",
        "",
        "He simply rolled a jar",
        "across the floor."
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        "A hollow sound",
        "echoed through the workshop.",
        "",
        "“Empty.”",
        "",
        "After a moment,",
        "he murmured,",
        "",
        "“Just like you.”"
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        "The jar kept rolling,",
        "without direction.",
        "",
        "“Lost.”",
        "",
        "“Like you.”",
        "",
        "Anger rose within him.",
        "",
        "But—"
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        "as the jar rolled to him",
        "and came to a stop,",
        "",
        "something deep within his chest",
        "quietly cracked.",
        "",
        "“…”",
        "",
        "After that day,",
        "Sad-Fist was seen no more."
      ]
    },
    {
      "lines": [
        "And then—",
        "",
        "a figure appeared,",
        "wearing a jar upon his head,",
        "calling himself by a new name.",
        "",
        "Jar-Fist."
      ]
    }
  ]
}